# Design System Rules

## Color Tokens

Use semantic color tokens instead of raw Tailwind palette classes.

- `text-ink`, `text-ink-secondary`, `text-ink-muted` — NOT `text-slate-*` or `text-gray-*`
- `bg-surface`, `bg-surface-alt`, `bg-parchment` — NOT `bg-white`, `bg-slate-*`, `bg-gray-*`
- `border-edge`, `border-edge-strong` — NOT `border-slate-*`, `border-gray-*`
- `text-brand`, `bg-brand-light` for links and brand accents
- `text-accent`, `bg-accent-light` for warm copper accent
- `text-valid`, `bg-valid-light` for success / validation
- `text-caution`, `bg-caution-light` for warnings
- `text-danger`, `bg-danger-light` for errors / retractions

Exception: item-type badges and tag colors use Tailwind's built-in palette at the -50/-800 range (blue, violet, emerald, amber, rose, cyan, orange, teal).

## Typography

Four font stacks, assigned by role:

- `font-display` (Playfair Display) — page titles, h1-h4
- `font-body` (Source Serif 4) — body text, summaries, prose
- `font-ui` (Inter) — nav, badges, labels, form controls, metadata
- `font-data` (JetBrains Mono) — metrics, scores, tabular numbers

CSS rules in globals.css auto-assign: body→body, h1-h4→display, nav/button/input→ui. Use Tailwind font utilities to override when an element's context differs from its HTML semantics.

Do NOT use `font-sans` or `font-serif` — use the semantic names above.

## Spacing

- Page container: `max-w-7xl px-6 pt-22 pb-20`
- Section gap: `mb-10` or `mb-12`
- Card padding: `p-5` or `p-6`
- Card borders: `border border-edge` with `hover:border-edge-strong`

## Verification

Run `node --test tests/design-system.test.mjs` after any styling change. The test suite enforces token usage, font class patterns, and spacing.

